  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to examine the age and the neurodegenerative disease effects on
      social cognition. Secondary goals are to better understand the relationships between
      different component of social cognition, executive functioning, and behavior and describing
      the neuronal substrates associated to the alteration of the social cognition in ageing and
      dementia.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
